President Biden hosted Speaker Pelosi and Leader Schumer to discuss their plans for tackling inflation and lowering prices. They aim to transition from a historic economic recovery to stable, steady growth. The leaders discussed various strategies, such as reducing prescription drug and energy costs, to combat inflation. They also highlighted the unprecedented job and small business creation under their leadership. Additionally, they emphasized the importance of addressing the global issue of inflation that is impacting major economies and contributing to the historic deficit reduction.